nt||at|mitche:  Now - should N bid 3@S after the double?   After all, she has 9 HCP and a 5 card suit?  
When partner BALANCES  (as compared with a direct double),  you need to subtract 4 points or so from your hand.   
Your partner "borrowed" those 4 points to make his double.  
Think of it this way - a balancing double might be an ace -or more- lighter than a direct X.  
So no, N should not bid 3@S on this hand.

